NO PCBs Required

Why?
Whilst extensive, my schematic is not perfect, and for a project like an analog synthesiser, it is far more cost effective to build on protoboard or veroboard.
This will be an iterative design and building process, meaning I will be updating my schematic as I build and find more efficient systems/corrects mistakes in my design.
This iterative process is easily acheived with the flexible nature of protoboards which allow me to remove, move and add components as I go.
